## Call for Posters

We invite submissions of poster abstracts for the **IROS 2026 Workshop on Enhancing Dexterous Manipulation Through Haptic Feedback**.  
The goal of this poster session is to provide an informal forum where researchers can share ongoing work, early-stage ideas, and recent results related to the integration of **haptics, tactile sensing, and dexterous manipulation**.

Poster presentations will take place during the workshop poster session and networking period. The format is intended to encourage discussion and interaction between attendees, speakers, and presenters.

We particularly encourage submissions from **students, early-career researchers, and interdisciplinary teams** working at the intersection of robotics, haptics, perception, and human–robot interaction.

---

## Topics of Interest

Relevant topics include, but are not limited to:

- Haptic feedback for robotic manipulation  
- Tactile sensing and perception  
- Bio-inspired tactile systems  
- Slip detection and tactile event sensing  
- Dexterous robotic manipulation  
- Control strategies for dexterous manipulation  
- Learning-based control and policy optimization for manipulation  
- Teleoperation and human-in-the-loop manipulation  
- Human tactile perception and psychophysics  
- Haptic interfaces and wearable haptics  
- Tactile data processing and machine learning for touch  
- Applications of haptics in robotics, VR/AR, and telemanipulation
- Soft materials and structures for tactile interaction

---

## Submission Guidelines

Poster submissions should consist of:

**1. A 1-page abstract (PDF)** describing the work to be presented.

The abstract should include:

- Title  
- Author names and affiliations  
- A short description of the research contribution  
- Optional figures illustrating the approach or results  

**2. Graphical Summary (required)**

Authors must also submit a **graphical summary** representing the work.  
This image will be used for:

- the poster listing on the workshop website  
- the digital poster booklet distributed to workshop attendees  

The graphical summary should:

- clearly illustrate the main idea or contribution of the work  
- be provided as a **PNG or JPG file**  
- have sufficient resolution for web and booklet display

Accepted abstracts will be presented as posters during the workshop and will be listed on the workshop website.

